{
  "texts": [
    "Prior to learning multiagent, they initialized the Q-network using prior knowledge obtained from a single automated guided vehicle in a static environment, utilizing the A* algorithm.",
    "This initialization process allowed the agents to acquire a better understanding of the environment, leading to improved learning efficiency.",
    "Additionally, they incorporated predefined prior rules to encourage the agents to avoid unnecessary exploration in the DQN algorithm.",
    "Additionally, Wang et al. (2020) demonstrated that a Duel neural network (Duel-NN) structure can outperform DQN and DDQN in solving the MAPF problem.",
    "Duel-NN differs from DQN and DDQN by incorporating an additional stream, the advantage function, which combines with the value stream to output the value function."
  ]
}